<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fire 5, Mutiny 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Ante Razov scored two of Chicago's four
second-half goals as the Fire rallied to rout the Tampa Bay Mutiny
5-1 on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   Trailing 1-0, the hosts tied the game in the 26th minute, when
Peter Nowak took a return pass from Jesse Marsch and fired a shot
past Tampa Bay goalkeeper Scott Garlick from the edge of the
penalty area.
</P>
<P>
   The Fire (3-3-1) jumped ahead two minutes after halftime, as
forward John Wolyniec scored off a pass from Lubos Kubik, and Razov
made it 3-1 in the 53rd minute thanks to Diego Gutierrez's cross.
</P>
<P>
   Razov then assisted on Kubik's goal in the 71st minute and
capped the scoring with four minutes left with help from Nowak and
defender Evan Whitfield.
</P>
<P>
   Tampa Bay (4-4-0), which dropped to 0-4 on the road, took an
early lead when defender Steve Trittschuh scored his first goal of
the season in the 15th minute.
</P>
<P>
   Chicago started Chris Snitko in goal because Zach Thornton is
injured.
</P>
</TEXT>
