<HEADLINE> Chile Bus Collision Leaves 7 Dead  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) -- A pair of buses carrying tourists and
rural travelers collided head-on in central Chile Saturday, leaving
seven people dead and 33 injured, eight of them seriously, police
reported.
</P>
<P>
   Police said the tourist bus was carrying several Argentine
nationals to the Argentine city of Mendoza, just across the Andes
from central Chile. All the fatalities were among Chileans riding
on the other vehicle, a rural transportation bus, according to
police.
</P>
<P>
   The accident occurred near Cetemu, a town 80 miles north of
here.
</P>
<P>
   A preliminary report said the accident occurred when the rural
bus attempted to pass a truck, a police officer told the Associated
Press by telephone from the area.
