<HEADLINE> Tanzania President To Run Again  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAR ES SALAAM, Tanzania (AP) -- President Benjamin Mkapa said
Saturday he would seek re-election to another five-year term in
Tanzania's Oct. 29 presidential and legislative elections.
</P>
<P>
   Mkapa, a former journalist, ambassador to the United States and
Nigeria and foreign minister, first ran in October 1995 as the
candidate of the Chama Cha Mapinduzi party founded by the late
President Julius Nyerere. Tanzania's constitution limits presidents
to two terms.
</P>
<P>
   Mkapa, who is also CCM chairman, said he would go Sunday to
Dodoma, Tanzania's political capital, to pick up the filing forms.
But John Malecela, CCM vice-chairman, said the exercise was only a
formality, since Mkapa had the party's full backing to run for a
second term.
</P>
<P>
   So far, no one has stepped forward to challenge Mkapa in the
October race.
</P>
