<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Larry Flynt's Co. Has Magazine Mixup  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   AKRON, Ohio (AP) -- A woman who ordered a skateboarding magazine
as a gift for her 15-year-old son received an X-rated publication --
a mistake that angered both her and Larry Flynt, who owns both
magazines.
</P>
<P>
   ''I was horrified,'' Becky Barrington said. ''I don't want my
son seeing that stuff.''
</P>
<P>
   Flynt already has fired the employee whose mistake caused
Hustler Taboo magazine to be mailed to all subscribers of Big
Brother Skateboarding, a Flynt spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
   Jerry Awang, vice president of operations for Flynt's publishing
house, said his boss was ''livid'' over the switch.
</P>
<P>
   He would not say how many copies were mailed in error because
the company does not release circulation data.
</P>
<P>
   Barrington said the company apologized to her when she
complained, However, she plans to cancel the Big Brother
subscription for her son, Justin Noga, now that she knows who owns
the skateboarding magazine.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
