<HEADLINE> Last of Clinton White House Dinners  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton attends his last formal
dinner with White House journalists Saturday night, an event marked
over the past seven years by both humor and controversy.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, Clinton showed up late enough at the White House
Correspondents Association annual dinner to miss the presentation
of the group's Edgar Allan Poe Award to Michael Isikoff, the
Newsweek reporter who unearthed the Monica Lewinsky scandal.
</P>
<P>
   In the midst of the Lewinsky scandal in 1998, Clinton stole the
show with a string of one-liners at the dinner.
</P>
<P>
   And in 1997 the president got many laughs with humorous
references to White House coffees that became part of the
much-investigated fund-raising practices in his re-election
campaign.
</P>
</TEXT>
