Suns Beat Spurs 101-94
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   PHOENIX (AP) -- Todd Day scored all 16 of his points in the fourth quarter
and Penny Hardaway had his first playoff triple-double today as the Suns, down
by 10 points at the end of the third period, rallied to beat the San Antonio
Spurs 101-94. Phoenix leads the best-of-five series 2-1 and can clinch it with a
homecourt victory in Game 4 Tuesday night. Six Suns scored in double figures.
Shawn Marion had 16 points and 13 rebounds, while Rodney Rogers scored 15
points, Cliff Robinson 14 and Kevin Johnson 10.
