Mets Beat Rockies 13-6
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Todd Pratt, filling in for catcher Mike Piazza, who has a
bruised wrist, had his first career four-hit game as the New York Mets tied a
team record with 23 hits in a 13-6 win over the Colorado Rockies today. Edgardo
Alfonzo also had four hits, and Derek Bell and Todd Zeile added three apiece for
the Mets. Facing the Mets for the first time since being traded to Colorado in
January, Masato Yoshii (1-2) had his worst outing in five starts with the
Rockies. He gave up six runs and nine hits in 3 2-3 innings.
</P>
