<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-29 21:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mich. Man Kills Wife, 2 Others, Self  </HEADLINE>
By MIKE HOUSEHOLDER, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOUNT CLEMENS, Mich. (AP) -- A man apparently distraught over his
wife's decision to leave him shot and killed her and two others and
then killed himself, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Raeann Rice, who told family members that her husband, Michael
Rice, had pulled a gun on her several days earlier, returned to her
home about 1:30 p.m. Saturday with her sister and her sister's
boyfriend.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Rice's brother told police he was on a couch upstairs
and the four were down in the basement when he suddenly heard
screaming and six gunshots, Mount Clemens police Lt. Brian Krutell
said.
</P>
<P>
   The sister's boyfriend, Dane Baetz, stumbled upstairs and threw
a cellular telephone to Rice's brother and said: ''Call 911,''
Krutell said.
</P>
<P>
   The brother ran out of the house. Baetz staggered out and fell
on the front lawn. As police dragged Baetz, two more shots rang
out.
</P>
<P>
   Baetz, 38, was taken to Mount Clemens General Hospital and died
during surgery, hospital spokeswoman Sara Brown said.
</P>
<P>
   Police tried to reach the gunman by telephone but could not.
They threw several telephones into the house but got no answer.
Through an intercom on the telephones, all police could hear was
the television, Krutell said.
</P>
<P>
   About 6:15 p.m., members of a special weapons and tactics team
broke down the back door and saw the bodies of Rice and his wife at
the bottom of the stairs. The body of the woman's sister, Lisa
Balaze, 33, was found about 15 feet away.
</P>
<P>
   Balaze and Raeann Rice, 31, each were shot in the head in the
same area of the basement, Krutell said. Rice then dragged his
wife's body over to the foot of the stairs, stood over her and shot
himself in the head, authorities. He was found slumped over her.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is a very bad scene,'' Krutell said. ''Compounding the
sadness of it all is that there's a lot of family members that have
been here the whole time just around the block.''
</P>
<P>
   Rice, who is in his early 30s, had two children with Raeann
Rice. Rice also had two children from a previous marriage, Krutell
said. None of the children were inside the home at the time of the
shootings.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-04-29-00 2159 </TRAILER>
