<HEADLINE> Fusion 1, Revolution 1, OT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   FOXBORO, Mass. (AP) -- The Miami Fusion ended their scoreless
drought at 457 minutes but allowed the New England Revolution to
pull even with 21 minutes left as the Eastern Division co-leaders
tied 1-1 Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Miami (1-2-4) took the lead in the 52nd minute when midfielder
Henry Gutierrez one-touched an 18-yard shot over New England
goalkeeper Jeff Causey.
</P>
<P>
   New England, 1-0-2 at home and 0-2-2 on the road, tied it when
defender Brian Dunseth headed in a corner kick by John Harkes.
</P>
<P>
   Neither team had a good scoring chance in the two five-minute
overtime periods. It was the third straight overtime match for the
Revolution.
</P>
<P>
   New England had its best first-half opportunities off indirect
kicks, by Mauricio Ramos in the 13th minute and by Harkes 12
minutes later.
</P>
<P>
   The hosts also nearly gained the lead a minute into the second
half, but William Sunsing's header off Harkes' corner kick was
knocked off the goal line by Miami defender Martin Machon.
</P>
<P>
   Miami is winless in three road games.
</P>
