<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Hits Southern Taiwan  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) -- A moderate earthquake struck southern
Taiwan on Sunday, seismologists said. No damage or injuries were
immediately reported.
</P>
<P>
   The 4.5-magnitude quake was centered 18 miles north of the port
city of Kaohsiung, the Central Weather Bureau said. Kaohsiung is
about 120 miles south of the capital of Taipei.
</P>
<P>
   A 7.6-magnitude tremor hit central Taiwan on Sept. 21, 1999,
killing more than 2,300 people. More than 12,000 aftershocks and
tremors have rattled the island since the big quake.
</P>
<P>
   Located along the earthquake-prone Pacific Rim and crisscrossed
by 51 fault lines, scores of earthquakes hit Taiwan each year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
